  "profile": {
    "id": "u02_aarti",
    "user_name": "Aarti",
    "profession": "Medical student preparing for NEET PG",
    "mother_tongue": "Marathi",
    "interests": "Cooking, classical music, books",
    "engagement": "medium",
    "english_level": "B1",
    "personality": "earnest, slightly anxious about exams, opens up about study stress"
  },
  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, I hope your walk went well. How was your head feeling after it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It's fine, thank you! The walk helped a lot. I also cooked my favorite dal today, which made me feel better. How are you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Good to hear, walking and dal are both good medicine. What kind of dal did you make?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It was moong dal, with a bit of garam masala. I love how simple and soothing it is. I was reading a bit of a fiction book after cooking—do you ever read for fun?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds like a calm, warm combo ,  moong dal and fiction books. What kind of book are you into?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I mostly read classics—like Jane Austen or Tagore. They help me relax after long study hours. Sometimes I get so stressed about NEET PG, I just need to escape into another world. Have you read any good books lately?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, classics are a perfect escape. That balance between work and books is smart. What Tagore book are you into?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm reading _Ghare Baire_ right now—such deep thoughts on love and duty. It makes me think about my own life sometimes. But I should probably get back to my notes now… NEET PG is in a few weeks!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — Ghare Baire is a heavy read. Love how you balance books and studies. What notes are top of mind now?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Mainly physiology and pharmacology. They are so confusing sometimes! I watched a short lecture on renal system today, but I still feel like I need more clarity. Sometimes I wonder, am I prepared enough? 😣"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that, renal system is tricky, even for seniors. Small fix: we say \"I feel like I need more clarity.\" What part feels the heaviest right now?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The heaviest part is connecting the clinical aspects with the diagrams. I get confused about how the nephron works exactly. Also, remembering all the drug actions—like how diuretics affect different parts of the kidney. It’s a lot! 😟"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, nephrons and diuretics are dense. Diagrams are key, what helps you remember them best?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, I try to make small sketches in my notes, but I get distracted easily. Maybe I should watch another video or ask a friend to explain it. Thank you for caring, Maya! I think I should get back to it now… byee! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great, just take it step by step. Good luck with your study session — see you soon!"
    }
  ],
